=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_BinaryOpUGen_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring punchy attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -12.2550
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5115
  pitch_clarity: 11.5298
  inharmonicity: 0.0038
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -3.5199
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: BinaryOpUGen Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/BinaryOpUGen.html
// Tags: BinaryOpUGen, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
// trigger an envelope
(
{
    var trig;
    trig = SinOsc.ar(1) > 0.1;
    EnvGen.kr(Env.perc, trig, doneAction: Done.none) * SinOsc.ar(440, 0, 0.1)
}.play
) // > outputs 0 or 1
